OL,3,CNew tech used by rugby players to see
OL,4,Chow menstrual cycle impacts concussion
OL,6,FJo Perkins, Head Physio of the WRU
OL,7,Fwomen's squad, said: "Through a
OL,8,Fmenstrual cycle there's a fluctuation
OL,9,Fof Estrogen and Progesterone and with
OL,10,Fthat can give a variety of symptoms
OL,11,Fthroughout a cycle.
OL,13,F"In terms of concussion, there's
OL,14,Fpotentially some research that
OL,15,Fsuggests if a player is concussed in
OL,16,Fthe luteal phase, the later phase
OL,17,Fafter ovulation, that symptoms may be
OL,18,Fmore prolonged, and more severe in
OL,19,Fsome athletes."
